 or extra dependencies. However, since the dependency chain resolves to Netty 4.2.2.Final, the same JVM properties as before are necessary. I'll consider including Gradle settings for nativeTest runtimeArgs and note potential risks with vertx-auth-oauth2.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering server setup**\\n\\nI'm thinking about using a local loopback server since external HTTP can be quite brittle. It seems that for local verification, relying on Gradle with native setup might be the best approach. It's likely that this would give me more authoritative results during testing. I need to make sure that everything is configured correctly to take advantage of the local server's reliability, as that could definitely streamline the verification process while avoiding potential hiccups with external connections.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra Maven dependency or Docker image is needed for meaningful Vert.x Web Client coverage; loopback HTTP server tests are normal. However io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1 resolves Vert.x 5.0.1 with Netty 4.2.2.Final, so Java 25 native runtime tests need the same Netty unsafe-access system properties already used for 5.0.0.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For native test execution on JDK 25, ensure the generated test configuration passes runtime system properties: -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true. Prefer local loopback Vert.x HttpServer/WebClient coverage for GET/POST, JSON, forms/multipart, redirects, cookies/session, streaming, and caching. Do not rely on external HTTP services.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"vertx-auth-oauth2 is optional in the artifact POM; OAuth2-specific WebClient flows would require extra setup and are not necessary for core coverage.\",\n    \"Jackson databind/POJO mapping is not on the normal runtime classpath unless explicitly added; JsonObject/Buffer/String body codecs avoid that optional dependency.\",\n    \"The unsafe-access properties are tied to Netty 4.2.x behavior on JDK 25 native runs and should be verified by the local Gradle/native-image workflow.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0016f16f01dd2287016a402e9a4bb081978495cd69828bf441\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 572, "output": 833, "cacheRead": 18944, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20349, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782591119709, "responseId": "resp_0016f16f01dd2287016a402e9010948197900a476fa39c8190"}, "toolResults": []}
